abstract: The departure of Luo Chan is a setback for the News Corporation, which had licensed the MySpace brand name in China in an effort to expand its media and Internet presence.
snippet: The departure of Luo Chan is a setback for the News Corporation, which had licensed the MySpace brand name in China in an effort to expand its media and Internet presence.
lead_paragraph: The chief executive of MySpace China, the social networking site, has resigned slightly more than a year after bringing the site to China, people briefed on the matter said Monday.

headline.main: MySpace China Says Its Chief Will Resign
headline.print_headline: MySpace China Says Its Chief Will Resign
